						<summary>

						<p>The inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Akā[la]varshadēva.</hi> It is very badly damaged and there is no means of finding out whether it belongs to the period of Kṛishṇa II or Kṛishṇa III. The characters are, however, too late for Kṛishṇa I.</p>						

